<subSubSection id="C350B2B199238551E887FC72D64AF411" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E887FC72D76DF3C9" blockId="37.[151,1437,908,1151]" box="[151,572,908,935]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E887FC72D743F3C9" bold="true" box="[151,530,908,935]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
44.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7FC4FD144F3A5" blockId="37.[151,1437,908,1151]" box="[199,1045,944,971]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7FC4FD430F3A5" bold="true" box="[199,353,944,971]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe; also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99238551EA87FC4ED7ABF3A5" box="[663,762,945,971]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: four northern provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7FC2AD60BF459" blockId="37.[151,1437,908,1151]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7FC2AD47DF381" bold="true" box="[199,300,981,1007]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ecology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB999238551E923FC29D76AF381" authorityName="Dolichopodinae" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[307,571,982,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanus">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E923FC29D76AF381" box="[307,571,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Hercostomus germanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from most macrohabitat categories in 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99238551ECAEFC2AD071F381" box="[1214,1312,981,1007]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, except for the littoral zone and the dunes. In northwestern and central Europe, it is mainly found on 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB999238551EC9CFC06D1A5F47D" authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1830" box="[1164,1268,1017,1043]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Apiaceae</taxonomicName>
(often 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB999238551ED57FC05D58EF459" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Daucus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carota">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551ED57FC05D58EF459" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Daucus carota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in sunny sites along trails in open forests (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDB9CCB99238551EAD7FBE2D61FF459" author="Pollet, M." box="[711,846,1053,1079]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7FBBFD7AAF435" blockId="37.[151,1437,908,1151]" box="[199,763,1088,1115]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7FBBFD400F435" bold="true" box="[199,337,1088,1115]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
8.0 (fairly rare). Extremely rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7FB9BD64AF411" blockId="37.[151,1437,908,1151]" box="[199,795,1124,1151]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7FB9BD4D3F411" bold="true" box="[199,386,1124,1151]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Activity period.</emphasis>
May–September, with peak in June.
</paragraph>
